00:25:40,114 --> 00:25:43,868
- Help me!
- Come on!

246
00:25:45,745 --> 00:25:47,622
Come on.

247
00:25:59,509 --> 00:26:03,679
You call 911
and don't leave your name?

248
00:26:03,888 --> 00:26:08,476
- Even a dumb geezer knows ...
- Just move on. No one was killed.

249
00:26:08,684 --> 00:26:10,770
Ask him.

250
00:26:11,813 --> 00:26:15,358
Don't bark at me.
I didn't name you.

251
00:26:15,566 --> 00:26:19,529
We will. And if he can't,
we'll come back and ask you.

252
00:26:19,737 --> 00:26:26,619
Hey. I come from hell. My grandma
has got more attitude than you.

253
00:26:26,828 --> 00:26:30,581
Go shake down a 7-11
for a day-old wiener.

254
00:26:30,581 --> 00:26:35,169
There's a painting
of one of the guys.

255
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:43,511
- I've been praying for him.
- I'm on my way to the hospital.

256
00:26:43,719 --> 00:26:47,890
- Just watch the dog for tonight.
- No, no.

257
00:26:48,099 --> 00:26:51,018
- I'm sorry.
- Thanks.

258
00:26:52,478 --> 00:26:56,858
Old bitch. Damn dog.

259
00:26:59,986 --> 00:27:02,905
You're taking him!

260
00:27:02,905 --> 00:27:05,199
Get out of the way!

261
00:27:05,408 --> 00:27:08,327
Even the books.

262
00:27:09,162 --> 00:27:11,247
Wait!

263
00:27:11,873 --> 00:27:15,418
Do you want to say no to me?

264
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:24,385
I don't want to say nothing to you.

265
00:27:24,802 --> 00:27:31,267
Because I've never felt this crazy.
I almost want you to say no.

266
00:27:34,604 --> 00:27:36,689
Thanks for looking after him.

267
00:27:36,898 --> 00:27:43,988
- Hey! Where are you going?
- You don't want to mess with me.

268
00:27:43,988 --> 00:27:48,993
I can't take a dog.
Nobody's been in here before.

269
00:27:52,747 --> 00:27:55,249
Hey, Frank.

270
00:28:18,815 --> 00:28:22,151
One, two, three, four ...

271
00:28:41,963 --> 00:28:44,465
You're dead.

272
00:28:44,674 --> 00:28:48,636
We don't have no dog food here.

273
00:28:48,636 --> 00:28:53,224
You'll eat what we got.
What we eat.

274
00:29:02,400 --> 00:29:04,902
Don't you do anything!

275
00:29:19,709 --> 00:29:22,211
Where's the trust?

276
00:29:31,596 --> 00:29:34,932
Never a break.

277
00:30:06,839 --> 00:30:08,716
God!

278
00:30:08,925 --> 00:30:13,721
We're halfway through the show
and we haven't sold a painting.

279
00:30:13,930 --> 00:30:17,266
No, we can't reduce the price.

280
00:30:17,475 --> 00:30:22,480
- I'm in a free fall here.
- We can see him.

281
00:30:23,731 --> 00:30:27,068
I'll meet you in there, okay?

282
00:30:29,153 --> 00:30:31,239
Thank you.

283
00:30:33,950 --> 00:30:38,329
- How are you doing, great one?
- I haven't looked at myself yet.

284
00:30:38,538 --> 00:30:43,126
I figured
I could tell from your reaction.

285
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:47,922
- That bad?
- I talked to the doctor and ...

286
00:30:51,884 --> 00:30:57,932
It's not that bad. The doctors say
you'll be your old self again.

287
00:30:58,141 --> 00:31:02,520
The scars might ... Oh, shit!

288
00:31:08,359 --> 00:31:10,445
Jackie ...

289
00:31:10,445 --> 00:31:13,573
Hand me a mirror, please.

290
00:31:21,289 --> 00:31:25,251
Wait. I have a smaller one.

291
00:31:35,261 --> 00:31:38,598
So how are things, anyway?

292
00:31:38,598 --> 00:31:44,228
- How is Verdell?
- Mr. Udall ... taking care of him.

293
00:31:44,437 --> 00:31:50,067
- How could you? He'll hurt him.
- No, I promise.

294
00:31:50,276 --> 00:31:55,072
Not a chance. I own this guy.
Besides, there was nobody else.

295
00:31:55,281 --> 00:31:58,201
I'm always on the move and ...

296
00:31:58,409 --> 00:32:01,329
Trust me.

297
00:32:01,537 --> 00:32:06,125
- You are certain my dog is okay?
- Yes, your dog is fine.

298
00:32:13,007 --> 00:32:16,552
Waiting gives the devil time.

299
00:32:33,027 --> 00:32:35,947
Oh, my!

300
00:32:45,748 --> 00:32:48,668
Where did I go?

301
00:32:49,710 --> 00:32:52,839
- That's your dog?
- No.

302
00:32:53,881 --> 00:32:57,009
What are you doing with a dog?

303
00:32:57,427 --> 00:33:02,223
- Suckered in, set up.
- You're not worried he'll be taken?

304
00:33:04,725 --> 00:33:08,271
No, not until now.

305
00:33:08,479 --> 00:33:12,442
- Sorry.
- I'm going to sit here.

306
00:33:12,442 --> 00:33:14,944
Hey, puppy.

307
00:33:15,778 --> 00:33:19,323
It's so cute.

308
00:33:19,323 --> 00:33:22,452
I wonder what breed he is.

309
00:33:25,997 --> 00:33:30,793
He's a little dog. If Bryan's not
here, you can bring him in.

310
00:33:33,504 --> 00:33:36,215
How old are you?

311
00:33:36,215 --> 00:33:39,761
To guess by your eyes ... 50.

312
00:33:40,386 --> 00:33:44,557
By your eyes, I'd say you were kind.
So much for eyes.

313
00:33:44,766 --> 00:33:49,145
How old are you?
You brought it up. I'm curious.

314
00:33:49,353 --> 00:33:54,150
- Not that you're ugly.
- I can take the compliment.

315
00:33:54,358 --> 00:33:58,946
But my knees start knocking when
you turn on the charm full blast.

316
00:33:59,155 --> 00:34:02,700
What's with the dark?

317
00:34:05,203 --> 00:34:07,497
Dawn patrol.

318
00:34:07,497 --> 00:34:11,459
My son had
a full-blown attack.

319
00:34:11,459 --> 00:34:16,881
And for extra fun
they gave us the wrong antibiotics.

320
00:34:17,090 --> 00:34:19,801
No!

321
00:34:20,009 --> 00:34:24,180
It's bacon for the dog.

322
00:34:26,057 --> 00:34:30,228
Last week I was playing the piano
for him. And he likes it.

323
00:34:30,436 --> 00:34:36,901
So I decide
I'm going to make a little joke.

324
00:34:45,868 --> 00:34:50,039
It's a beautiful day for our walk.

325
00:35:02,135 --> 00:35:05,680
Look at that dog.

326
00:35:05,888 --> 00:35:10,893
I've got to give you
something real good.

327
00:35:11,310 --> 00:35:15,064
I'm going to show it to you.

328
00:35:16,315 --> 00:35:19,444
Don't be like me.

329
00:35:19,444 --> 00:35:25,283
Stay as you are. You're perfect.
I'll get you something to eat.

330
00:35:27,368 --> 00:35:30,496
I'd like to be treated like that.

331
00:35:31,956 --> 00:35:36,127
Let's go home and do some writing.

332
00:35:37,587 --> 00:35:42,175
"He had made the girl happy.
And what a girl."

333
00:35:42,592 --> 00:35:46,137
"You've saved my life, she said."

334
00:35:47,597 --> 00:35:51,142
"You'd better make it up to me."

335
00:35:53,853 --> 00:35:59,901
Done!
Yes, I hate the doggie.

336
00:36:01,152 --> 00:36:04,280
62 books. Done.

337
00:36:05,114 --> 00:36:10,536
- We have to cut back all expenses.
- He has no medical insurance?

338
00:36:10,745 --> 00:36:15,750
These are the food receipts,
the household expenses.

339
00:36:15,958 --> 00:36:19,712
- Here's one for the dog again.
- I got it.

340
00:36:19,921 --> 00:36:23,049
And all the laundry.

341
00:36:25,134 --> 00:36:32,016
Boy, look at that.
He likes it at Chez Melvin.

342
00:36:33,476 --> 00:36:37,855
What are you coming over here for?
I can't cook with a dog near me.

343
00:36:38,064 --> 00:36:44,529
Just sit. We don't want any company.
I'll read you Emerson.

344
00:36:56,207 --> 00:37:02,046
- How's Verdell doing?
- He's a pain in the ass.

345
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:12,473
Simon's home. Can you keep the dog
until he's had a chance to adjust?

346
00:37:12,682 --> 00:37:17,270
It's been weeks and weeks.
A few more won't matter.

347
00:37:17,478 --> 00:37:22,900
He wants him back right away.
He'll be by tomorrow.

348
00:37:24,777 --> 00:37:28,531
Okay.

349
00:37:33,953 --> 00:37:37,290
Hungry? Be right with you.

350
00:38:40,686 --> 00:38:42,772
Mr. Udall.

351
00:38:48,194 --> 00:38:52,573
Some face they left hanging on you.
You look like ...

352
00:38:52,782 --> 00:38:56,536
Could you take it ...

353
00:38:57,578 --> 00:39:00,706
... just a little easy, Mr. Udall?

354
00:39:04,043 --> 00:39:05,920
Thank you.

355
00:39:08,631 --> 00:39:11,134
Verdell.

356
00:39:12,593 --> 00:39:16,764
Come here, my beautiful boy.
Come here.

357
00:39:16,764 --> 00:39:20,309
Let's go home and get well.

358
00:39:21,352 --> 00:39:26,357
I can't blame him for being weird.
Look at yourself in the mirror.

359
00:39:30,945 --> 00:39:33,030
Thank you.

360
00:39:36,367 --> 00:39:39,287
Come on, sweetheart.

361
00:39:39,495 --> 00:39:42,832
Verdell, come here.

362
00:39:44,917 --> 00:39:48,045
I know what you want.

363
00:39:51,591 --> 00:39:54,093
Where's my boy?

364
00:39:59,724 --> 00:40:03,478
No, don't force him.

365
00:40:35,176 --> 00:40:39,555
Over a dog!

366
00:40:40,181 --> 00:40:43,726
Over an ugly dog.

367
00:40:51,025 --> 00:40:55,613
Worst sidewalk in New York.
Look where they put it.

368
00:41:02,286 --> 00:41:07,083
- Help!
- You'll make an appointment.

369
00:41:07,291 --> 00:41:11,254
How can you diagnose someone as
an obsessive-compulsive disorder -

370
00:41:11,462 --> 00:41:14,590
- and then act like I had a choice
about barging in?

371
00:41:14,590 --> 00:41:18,136
- You must leave.
- You said you could help me.

372
00:41:18,344 --> 00:41:23,766
- What was that? A tease?
- If you take responsibility ...

373
00:41:23,975 --> 00:41:27,937
- You changed the room around.
- Two years ago.

374
00:41:28,146 --> 00:41:32,108
I also grew a beard, but you're
not interested in changes in me.

375
00:41:32,316 --> 00:41:36,279
I don't have a mountain of time.
I have to get to my restaurant.

376
00:41:36,487 --> 00:41:40,658
Do you know how hard it was for me
to come here?

377
00:41:42,118 --> 00:41:44,412
No, we're not doing this now.

378
00:41:44,620 --> 00:41:49,834
I changed just one pattern,
as you always said I should.

379
00:41:50,042 --> 00:41:52,336
No. Nope.

380
00:42:01,721 --> 00:42:06,517
What if this is
as good as it gets?

381
00:42:18,196 --> 00:42:21,324
What the heck are those for?

382
00:42:23,409 --> 00:42:26,537
No, no, no. Get Carol.

383
00:42:26,537 --> 00:42:32,376
I'm filling in. She might be getting
a job closer to home.

384
00:42:34,670 --> 00:42:39,050
- Why plastic?
- What are you trying to do to me?

385
00:42:39,258 --> 00:42:43,429
- What do you mean?
- Look, elephant girl.

386
00:42:43,638 --> 00:42:49,268
Go get Carol or something.
Just have her do my one meal here.

387
00:42:49,268 --> 00:42:52,396
I'll pay whatever you want.

388
00:42:54,690 --> 00:42:57,193
Do it!

389
00:42:59,695 --> 00:43:03,241
Bryan. Code blue.

390
00:43:08,454 --> 00:43:12,834
Out! Just shut up and get out.

391
00:43:13,668 --> 00:43:19,715
I'll be quiet.
Just let me stay here. No problem.

392
00:43:19,924 --> 00:43:24,303
Go get Carol.

393
00:43:24,720 --> 00:43:29,934
I'm not a prick.
You are. I'm not judging.

394
00:43:30,143 --> 00:43:35,356
This day has been a disaster.

395
00:43:35,982 --> 00:43:39,944
- I'm not sure if I can handle this.
- Get out!

396
00:43:40,987 --> 00:43:47,452
Get out immediately
or there's going to be trouble.

397
00:44:02,675 --> 00:44:04,760
See you.

398
00:44:05,803 --> 00:44:08,097
It's about time.

399
00:44:09,974 --> 00:44:15,396
- Carol's last name?
- Connelly.

400
00:44:23,112 --> 00:44:27,074
- Does he visit often?
- Not really. Not any more.

401
00:45:17,542 --> 00:45:20,253
I'm hungry.

402
00:45:20,461 --> 00:45:23,798
You've ruined my whole day.
I haven't eaten.

403
00:45:24,006 --> 00:45:27,969
- What are you doing here?
- This is not a sexist thing ...

404
00:45:28,177 --> 00:45:31,722
Are you totally gone?
This is my home.

405
00:45:33,808 --> 00:45:39,439
I'm trying to keep emotion aside,
even though it's important.

406
00:45:39,647 --> 00:45:44,652
- I have strong feelings on this.
- What?

407
00:45:44,652 --> 00:45:50,700
That I wasn't there? Do you have
any control over how creepy you get?

408
00:45:56,539 --> 00:46:00,293
Yes, I do.

409
00:46:01,127 --> 00:46:06,966
And to prove it ... I have not
gotten personal, and you have.

410
00:46:07,592 --> 00:46:11,971
Why aren't you at work?
Are you sick?

411
00:46:14,056 --> 00:46:17,602
You don't look sick.

412
00:46:18,019 --> 00:46:21,773
Just tired and bitter.

413
00:46:23,858 --> 00:46:26,986
My son is sick.

414
00:46:29,489 --> 00:46:32,408
What about your mother?

415
00:46:32,825 --> 00:46:38,456
- How do you know about her?
- I hear you talking while I wait.

416
00:46:38,664 --> 00:46:42,627
- Mom, I finished my juice.
- One sec.

417
00:46:51,803 --> 00:46:54,096
How are you doing?

418
00:46:59,727 --> 00:47:02,021
You should answer me.

419
00:47:02,230 --> 00:47:07,026
Sorry, Melvin. I can't handle you
teaching my son manners.

420
00:47:09,946 --> 00:47:12,448
Back to life.

421
00:47:19,956 --> 00:47:22,667
What's wrong?

422
00:47:22,875 --> 00:47:29,132
Five one-thousand,
four one-thousand ...

423
00:47:32,051 --> 00:47:36,013
- 104.9.
- We're going on a cab ride.

424
00:47:38,099 --> 00:47:41,436
Look out, you guys!

425
00:47:42,478 --> 00:47:46,858
Look out.
We're okay. We're okay.

426
00:47:48,526 --> 00:47:51,237
Melvin! Wait!

427
00:47:52,071 --> 00:47:55,199
Melvin! Wait!

428
00:48:00,830 --> 00:48:04,167
Shut up, kids!

429
00:48:04,584 --> 00:48:07,712
Give us a lift, would you?

430
00:48:11,883 --> 00:48:15,219
Cover your mouth when you cough.

431
00:48:17,096 --> 00:48:22,518
- Brooklyn Presbyterian Hospital.
- Hospital?

432
00:48:23,144 --> 00:48:28,357
- Any chance you'll be back today?
- No! Stay away from me.

433
00:48:32,945 --> 00:48:38,785
We can't put this off any longer.
I feel terrible that I have to ...

434
00:48:39,202 --> 00:48:43,581
Could you just leave the dog
for a second?

435
00:48:45,249 --> 00:48:48,169
Sorry.

436
00:48:50,880 --> 00:48:56,093
- What are those cards?
- Frank thought I should have notes.

437
00:48:56,928 --> 00:49:01,933
So I would maintain focus
and not terrify you.

438
00:49:02,141 --> 00:49:07,563
See? He's right.
I need the cards.

439
00:49:07,772 --> 00:49:09,440
SIMON, YOU'RE BROKE

440
00:49:16,114 --> 00:49:21,119
The medical bills are 61,000 now.
And the show didn't go well.

441
00:49:21,327 --> 00:49:26,124
I spoke to your parents.
They didn't hang up or anything.

442
00:49:26,332 --> 00:49:30,294
But they'd feel strange calling you.

443
00:49:30,503 --> 00:49:35,091
I can't call them. Come here, baby.

444
00:49:36,342 --> 00:49:38,219
Come here.

445
00:49:38,427 --> 00:49:42,390
Verdell? What's wrong?

446
00:49:42,598 --> 00:49:46,978
You miss the tough guy?
Well, here I am.

447
00:49:47,186 --> 00:49:52,191
Happy to see me, you little mop?
How about a ride down the chute?

448
00:49:52,400 --> 00:49:55,111
I'm sorry. I didn't mean that.

449
00:49:55,319 --> 00:49:58,030
I didn't mean that, sweetheart.

450
00:49:58,239 --> 00:49:59,907
Sorry ...

451
00:50:01,367 --> 00:50:06,789
I'll be able to keep my apartment
and the studio, won't I?

452
00:50:09,500 --> 00:50:13,463
Oh, my God!

453
00:50:43,284 --> 00:50:47,663
Yes, you make us a lot of money.
But it's more appropriate ...

454
00:50:47,872 --> 00:50:54,754
I need this.
Just say, "Melvin, I'll try."

455
00:50:57,465 --> 00:51:01,427
- Melvin, I'll try.
- Thank you.

456
00:51:01,636 --> 00:51:07,892
My son just got accepted to Brown.
My husband was dying.

457
00:51:08,100 --> 00:51:13,940
Good, nice, thrilled, exciting.
You don't have to wait with me.

458
00:51:21,864 --> 00:51:29,372
I can't resist. I just have
so many questions I want to ask you.

459
00:51:29,580 --> 00:51:33,751
You have no idea
what your work means to me.

460
00:51:33,960 --> 00:51:36,462
What does it mean to you?

461
00:51:36,879 --> 00:51:41,467
That somebody out there knows
what it's like to be in here.

462
00:51:42,718 --> 00:51:45,012
God, this is like a nightmare.

463
00:51:45,847 --> 00:51:49,809
Come on.
Just a couple of questions.

464
00:51:53,146 --> 00:51:57,525
- How do you write women so well?
- I think of a man.

465
00:51:57,733 --> 00:52:02,321
And I take away reason
and accountability.

466
00:52:33,811 --> 00:52:36,105
- Mom!
- In here, Mrs. Connelly.

467
00:52:36,314 --> 00:52:39,442
- Please, what?
- I'm ...

468
00:52:39,650 --> 00:52:42,361
- Tell me!
- Dr. Bettes.

469
00:52:42,570 --> 00:52:47,366
- Not your name. Where is he?
- He's in the bathroom.

470
00:52:47,992 --> 00:52:52,371
What's wrong? You know there are
doctors that come to your house?

471
00:52:52,580 --> 00:52:55,500
I'm home.

472
00:52:55,500 --> 00:52:59,879
I didn't know you had an admirer.
Oh, you met the gift.

473
00:53:01,130 --> 00:53:04,258
He's good. I'm an expert on doctors.

474
00:53:04,467 --> 00:53:07,595
Okay, doctor?

475
00:53:07,595 --> 00:53:11,349
My wife is
Melvin Udall's publisher.

476
00:53:11,557 --> 00:53:16,979
I'm to take care of this little guy
because you are needed at work.

477
00:53:17,188 --> 00:53:21,359
- What kind of work do you do?
- I'm a waitress.

478
00:53:21,567 --> 00:53:25,530
- In Manhattan.
- Dr. Bettes?

479
00:53:25,738 --> 00:53:28,241
Excuse me.

480
00:53:29,909 --> 00:53:34,080
- I'm sorry it took so long.
- I couldn't find it, either.

481
00:53:34,288 --> 00:53:40,753
Could you get this to the lab?
I want it back today.

482
00:53:40,962 --> 00:53:47,009
- Did you say "today"?
- Yes. Let's sit down.

483
00:53:48,052 --> 00:53:53,474
These are the receipts from
all the prescriptions for the year.

484
00:53:53,683 --> 00:53:59,313
- The calendar.
- This is a calendar of days.

485
00:53:59,522 --> 00:54:02,650
- And how he felt.
- Good.

486
00:54:02,859 --> 00:54:07,447
- How long has he had the problem?
- Since forever. Six months old.

487
00:54:07,655 --> 00:54:10,366
Have they done blood tests?

488
00:54:10,575 --> 00:54:14,328
- When he was well?
- No.

