968
01:51:35,061 --> 01:51:39,857
It was odd that you didn't come and
see me when you heard I was hurt.

969
01:51:40,066 --> 01:51:42,777
<i>- We almost did.</i>
- I don't want to talk about it.

970
01:51:42,985 --> 01:51:47,573
The important thing is
that your son is happy.

971
01:51:47,573 --> 01:51:50,910
- I'm working again.
<i>- Good. About money ...

972
01:51:51,118 --> 01:51:58,209
No. I'll drop you a line. It's up
to you to make the next move.

973
01:51:58,417 --> 01:52:03,631
He's going to want to stay.
And they'll take a ride to the lake.

974
01:52:04,465 --> 01:52:09,262
- Bye-bye.
<i>- Goodbye, dear.

975
01:52:10,513 --> 01:52:15,309
We'll probably have a five-hour
drive. It'll give us a chance to ...

976
01:52:16,978 --> 01:52:20,523
- I'm coming.
- What about your parents?

977
01:52:20,731 --> 01:52:24,485
- No. I'll take care of myself.
- What are you talking about?

978
01:52:24,694 --> 01:52:29,907
- You've got real problems.
- I know. I'm a little bit nervous.

979
01:52:29,907 --> 01:52:33,661
Suddenly everything seems so easy.

980
01:52:34,078 --> 01:52:37,623
Carol, a load has been lifted.

981
01:52:40,126 --> 01:52:43,462
- One night wih me.
- You think you're kidding.

982
01:52:47,425 --> 01:52:52,847
- No choice.
- I've got a gift for you.

983
01:52:52,847 --> 01:52:56,809
Let me see ... Gorgeous.

984
01:52:57,643 --> 01:53:02,440
Do it. And get the dog picked up. I
can't believe he let it stay there.

985
01:53:02,648 --> 01:53:05,359
Goodbye.

986
01:53:05,568 --> 01:53:07,653
Your luck's running.

987
01:53:07,862 --> 01:53:13,075
They sub-let your place.
You're homeless.

988
01:53:13,284 --> 01:53:18,915
- Frank's got a line on a new place.
- Where?

989
01:53:19,540 --> 01:53:23,085
Does it matter?

990
01:53:24,128 --> 01:53:27,256
No, it doesn't.

991
01:53:28,090 --> 01:53:31,219
I'm fine. Like the hat?

992
01:53:32,261 --> 01:53:34,138
I'm sorry.

993
01:53:49,153 --> 01:53:51,656
FOR EMERGENCY USE ONLY

994
01:54:06,879 --> 01:54:12,093
- I don't want to hear that music.
- You said you liked it.

995
01:54:14,595 --> 01:54:20,851
- This one has a meaning.
- I don't want to hear it.

996
01:54:43,165 --> 01:54:47,336
Here's the keys to my apartment.

997
01:54:47,545 --> 01:54:51,716
Go up there and wait
and I'll take Carol home.

998
01:54:51,924 --> 01:54:56,512
- I'll take a bus.
- No, I'll take you.

999
01:55:01,934 --> 01:55:04,854
Can you come here?

1000
01:55:05,062 --> 01:55:08,816
- I don't care what you did for me.
- What's wrong?

1001
01:55:09,025 --> 01:55:14,238
I don't want to know you any more.
All you do is make me feel bad.

1002
01:55:17,783 --> 01:55:20,703
You have my number.

1003
01:55:21,954 --> 01:55:26,125
- Let him take you home.
- Don't want to.

1004
01:55:27,376 --> 01:55:30,504
- I love you.
- I love you too.

1005
01:55:38,846 --> 01:55:41,766
Don't say anything.

1006
01:55:45,311 --> 01:55:50,733
I've got to get a hold of Frank
and see where I'm hanging my hat.

1007
01:55:51,776 --> 01:55:55,321
I think you're going to
have to camp it here.

1008
01:55:55,529 --> 01:55:58,866
There's Verdell!

1009
01:56:06,999 --> 01:56:10,753
Mommy and Daddy are home.

1010
01:56:12,213 --> 01:56:16,384
Sorry. You're fun to mess with.

1011
01:56:17,635 --> 01:56:22,848
They rented your place furnished.
Jackie said she'd bring your things.

1012
01:56:23,057 --> 01:56:28,062
They were going to set you up
in here. It's an extra room.

1013
01:56:28,062 --> 01:56:33,067
- It's got good light.
- I'm coming.

1014
01:56:38,072 --> 01:56:42,034
It's nice. Looks good.

1015
01:56:42,243 --> 01:56:49,959
They've even got your music,
paintings, paints.

1016
01:56:49,959 --> 01:56:52,461
I have to say they did a good job.

1017
01:56:55,381 --> 01:57:01,429
It's going to be okay.
Cosy, huh?

1018
01:57:06,225 --> 01:57:10,813
Thank you, Melvin.
You overwhelm me.

1019
01:57:18,112 --> 01:57:21,866
I love you.

1020
01:57:26,037 --> 01:57:32,710
I'd be the luckiest guy alive
if that did it for me.

1021
01:57:44,805 --> 01:57:48,351
Make yourself at home.

1022
01:57:49,810 --> 01:57:52,313
Anything else in the bag?

1023
01:57:52,521 --> 01:57:56,275
But I was playing soccer
while you were away.

1024
01:57:56,484 --> 01:58:00,029
I love my cookbook.

1025
01:58:00,238 --> 01:58:05,243
It's got wonderful recipes.
It says something with a shark.

1026
01:58:05,243 --> 01:58:10,665
Shark with a bite.
Would you like that, Spencer?

1027
01:58:10,665 --> 01:58:13,376
And some cookies here
called Wasps' Nests.

1028
01:58:16,921 --> 01:58:20,258
Where is my big hairy boy?

1029
01:58:20,466 --> 01:58:25,263
Where is he?
Where is my beautiful boy?

1030
01:58:25,471 --> 01:58:27,765
Sweetheart!

1031
01:58:27,765 --> 01:58:31,310
- Oh, you're in bed.
- No, no.

1032
01:58:34,647 --> 01:58:41,946
I just didn't think Verdell should
get too comfortable sleeping here.

1033
01:58:42,154 --> 01:58:45,700
The dog's already comfortable.

1034
01:58:49,662 --> 01:58:51,747
Is this okay?

1035
01:58:53,624 --> 01:58:57,169
Hello ... Hi, it's me.

1036
01:58:57,587 --> 01:59:03,009
He took me in.
It's Carol for you.

1037
01:59:03,009 --> 01:59:08,014
- Jackie brought it all over ...
- Just take the dog.

1038
01:59:08,848 --> 01:59:10,933
Take the dog.

1039
01:59:14,270 --> 01:59:19,692
- Come on. Move fast. Don't limp.
- Good luck.

1040
01:59:36,167 --> 01:59:39,295
<i>- How are you doing?</i>
- Not so hot.

1041
01:59:39,503 --> 01:59:45,134
<i>- Why? What's wrong?</i>
- Was I sensible or hard on you?

1042
01:59:45,551 --> 01:59:51,807
<i>- Maybe both.</i>
- Are you being cute or crazy now?

1043
01:59:52,016 --> 01:59:56,604
- Cute.
- You don't have to answer.

1044
01:59:56,812 --> 01:59:59,315
Just listen to me.

1045
01:59:59,941 --> 02:00:04,320
It's really something
that you're looking after Simon.

1046
02:00:04,528 --> 02:00:10,159
And what I said on the street ...
That was a bad thing to say.

1047
02:00:10,368 --> 02:00:16,415
It made me sick to my stomach.
It was a bad thing to say.

1048
02:00:16,832 --> 02:00:21,629
And I'd be lying if I didn't say
I enjoy your company.

1049
02:00:23,089 --> 02:00:29,345
But you do bother me.
And I know it's better for me ...

1050
02:00:29,554 --> 02:00:34,141
... to not have contact with you
because you're not ready.

1051
02:00:34,350 --> 02:00:38,729
You're an old guy to not be ready.
And I'm too old to ignore that.

1052
02:00:38,938 --> 02:00:44,569
But there were extraordinary
kindnesses that did take place.

1053
02:00:51,242 --> 02:00:54,370
Anyway. Thanks for the trip.

1054
02:00:56,038 --> 02:00:58,332
Goodnight.

1055
02:00:58,541 --> 02:01:01,669
Okay if I say something now?

1056
02:01:05,631 --> 02:01:08,342
Go ahead.

1057
02:01:09,385 --> 02:01:13,556
I should have danced with you.

1058
02:01:16,475 --> 02:01:20,021
Goodnight.

1059
02:01:39,624 --> 02:01:44,212
- Are you going to talk to me?
- I'm coming.

1060
02:01:54,639 --> 02:01:59,644
- What did she say?
- That I'm a great guy.

1061
02:01:59,852 --> 02:02:04,023
And she doesn't want
contact with me.

1062
02:02:05,274 --> 02:02:07,985
I'm dying here.

1063
02:02:09,445 --> 02:02:15,284
- Because ... you love her.
- No.

1064
02:02:15,493 --> 02:02:18,621
And you people
are supposed to be sensitive?

1065
02:02:18,829 --> 02:02:23,209
Then you tell me why.
You're the one who's "dying here".

1066
02:02:23,417 --> 02:02:27,171
- Let me sleep on it.
- Oh, come on.

1067
02:02:27,380 --> 02:02:31,133
- I'll figure it out.
- Please ...

1068
02:02:32,593 --> 02:02:38,849
I'm stuck.
I can't get back to my old life.

1069
02:02:40,935 --> 02:02:45,940
- She's evicted me from my life.
- Did you really like it that much?

1070
02:02:46,148 --> 02:02:49,277
It's better than this.

1071
02:02:49,485 --> 02:02:53,864
If you're going to give me hope,
you've got to do better.

1072
02:02:54,073 --> 02:02:58,035
If you can't be mildly interesting,
then shut up.

1073
02:02:58,244 --> 02:03:02,206
I'm drowning here!
And you're describing the water.

1074
02:03:02,415 --> 02:03:05,334
Picking on me won't help.

1075
02:03:06,586 --> 02:03:10,339
If that's true,
I'm really in trouble.

1076
02:03:10,548 --> 02:03:14,719
Do you know where you're lucky?

1077
02:03:19,307 --> 02:03:23,060
You know who you want.

1078
02:03:23,269 --> 02:03:29,317
I would take your seat any day.
Do something. Go over there.

1079
02:03:29,525 --> 02:03:34,739
Tonight. It's not always good
to let things calm down.

1080
02:03:34,947 --> 02:03:38,910
You can do this, Melvin.

1081
02:03:39,118 --> 02:03:42,246
Tell her how you feel.

1082
02:03:42,455 --> 02:03:46,834
- I'm charged.
- Yes, you are.

1083
02:03:46,834 --> 02:03:51,631
- She might kill me if I go there.
- Then stay. I'll read you a story.

1084
02:03:51,631 --> 02:03:57,470
The best thing going for you is your
willingness to humiliate yourself.

1085
02:03:57,678 --> 02:04:01,432
Go over there.
Do this. Catch her off guard.

1086
02:04:11,234 --> 02:04:13,945
Thanks a lot.

1087
02:04:15,613 --> 02:04:18,324
Here I go.

1088
02:04:27,500 --> 02:04:30,211
What's wrong?

1089
02:04:31,879 --> 02:04:35,007
I forgot to lock the door.

1090
02:05:53,210 --> 02:05:56,756
- What do you want?
- I'm sorry I woke you up.

1091
02:05:56,964 --> 02:06:00,301
I wasn't asleep.

1092
02:06:03,638 --> 02:06:06,557
What a break.

1093
02:06:07,600 --> 02:06:11,354
Is it a secret
what you're doing here?

1094
02:06:13,439 --> 02:06:16,567
I had to see you.

1095
02:06:19,695 --> 02:06:21,989
Because?

1096
02:06:24,283 --> 02:06:28,454
It relaxes me.

1097
02:06:28,871 --> 02:06:33,042
I'd feel better sitting outside
your apartment on the curb -

1098
02:06:33,251 --> 02:06:37,630
- than any other place
I can think of or imagine.

1099
02:06:37,838 --> 02:06:40,341
That's overstating.

1100
02:06:40,550 --> 02:06:46,389
I'd rather be sitting inside so l
don't get my feet in the gutter.

1101
02:06:46,597 --> 02:06:52,228
Stop. Why can't I just have
a normal boyfriend? Why?

1102
02:06:52,228 --> 02:06:55,982
A regular boyfriend
who doesn't go nuts on me.

1103
02:06:56,190 --> 02:06:59,527
Everybody wants that.
It doesn't exist.

1104
02:07:03,281 --> 02:07:08,286
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to interrupt.

1105
02:07:14,542 --> 02:07:17,670
Boyfriend ...

1106
02:07:20,590 --> 02:07:25,803
Come on in and try
not to ruin everything by being you.

1107
02:07:26,012 --> 02:07:30,182
Maybe we could live
without the wisecracks?

1108
02:07:33,519 --> 02:07:37,273
Maybe we could.

1109
02:08:02,298 --> 02:08:07,303
It feels a little confined here.
Let's take a walk.

1110
02:08:10,223 --> 02:08:15,645
It's four in the morning.
A walk sounds a little screwy to me.

1111
02:08:16,687 --> 02:08:21,692
- If you don't mind.
- Well, if you need an excuse ...

1112
02:08:22,526 --> 02:08:26,697
There's a bakery on the corner
that'll be open soon.

1113
02:08:26,906 --> 02:08:32,745
That way we're not screwy,
but two people that like warm rolls.

1114
02:08:57,144 --> 02:09:03,401
- What are you doing?
- I want you to hear that song.

1115
02:09:10,908 --> 02:09:15,705
<i>And darling</i>
<i>I'm never lonely

1116
02:09:15,913 --> 02:09:19,458
<i>whenever you're in sight...

1117
02:09:20,293 --> 02:09:22,169
Thank you.

1118
02:09:23,629 --> 02:09:26,966
I was ...

1119
02:09:40,938 --> 02:09:46,152
I'm sorry.
Whatever this is won't work.

1120
02:09:54,493 --> 02:09:56,996
- I'm ...
- What?

1121
02:09:59,081 --> 02:10:02,001
I'm feeling better.

1122
02:10:02,209 --> 02:10:09,091
It may seem that way now,
but you don't know me all that well.

1123
02:10:09,926 --> 02:10:12,845
I'm not the answer for you.

1124
02:10:13,054 --> 02:10:17,225
- I've got a compliment for you.
- You know what?

1125
02:10:17,433 --> 02:10:21,187
Let me talk.

1126
02:10:27,860 --> 02:10:31,614
I might be the only person
on the earth -

1127
02:10:31,822 --> 02:10:34,742
- that knows
you're the greatest woman on earth.

1128
02:10:34,951 --> 02:10:42,458
I might be the only one who knows
how amazing you are.

1129
02:10:42,875 --> 02:10:47,046
And how you are with Spencer.
Spence.

1130
02:10:48,297 --> 02:10:52,468
And in every single thought
you have.

1131
02:10:52,677 --> 02:10:59,350
How you almost always mean something
that's about being straight or good.

1132
02:11:00,601 --> 02:11:04,564
Most people miss that about you.

1133
02:11:04,772 --> 02:11:09,986
I wonder how they can watch you
bring their food and clear tables -

1134
02:11:10,194 --> 02:11:14,365
- and never get that they just met
the greatest woman alive.

1135
02:11:14,574 --> 02:11:19,787
And the fact that I get it
makes me feel good ...

1136
02:11:20,621 --> 02:11:25,001
... about me.

1137
02:11:31,257 --> 02:11:37,722
Is that something
that it's bad for you to be around?

1138
02:11:46,898 --> 02:11:49,400
No.

1139
02:11:52,111 --> 02:11:55,448
I'm going to grab you?

1140
02:11:55,656 --> 02:12:00,244
I didn't mean for that to be
a question. I'm going to grab you.

1141
02:12:23,809 --> 02:12:26,520
I know I can do better than that.

1142
02:12:50,086 --> 02:12:53,839
Better. Definitely better.

1143
02:12:58,010 --> 02:13:00,930
See?

1144
02:13:14,902 --> 02:13:19,699
- Want something?
- Warm rolls.

1145
02:13:28,249 --> 02:13:30,334
Excuse us.
